  <li><link href="https://fizzyelt.github.io/functional-programming/" type="external">帶你入門 functional programming</link></li></ul></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>43588</anchor> <rss>jms-006Z.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Changelog</taxon> <addr>jms-006Z</addr>  <route>jms-006Z.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>14</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Forester 2.3</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p><link href="armaëlguéneau.xml" type="local" addr="armaëlguéneau" title="Armaël Guéneau">Armaël Guéneau</link>, <link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local" addr="rileyshahar" title="Riley Shahar">Riley Shahar</link>, and <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" addr="jonmsterling" title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</link> contributed code to this major release. Thanks also to <link href="masanoriogino.xml" type="local" addr="masanoriogino" title="Masanori Ogino">Masanori Ogino</link> for <link href="jms-0072.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0072" title="Forester 2.3 › rudimentary support for XML attributes">feature requests</link> that made it into this release.</p><p>This release adds some new features to the command line interface. The original behavior of the <code>forester</code> command is now obtained by calling <code>forester build</code>. Please browse <code>forester --help</code> for more information.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>43589</anchor> <rss>jms-0070.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0070</addr>  <route>jms-0070.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>14</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="jms-006Z.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006Z" title="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</link> › create new trees from the command line</title> <parent>jms-006Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A new command has been added in <link href="jms-006Z.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006Z" title="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</link> to simplify the creation of new trees with the correct base-36 identifier. If your personal namespace prefix is <code>xxx</code>, you may run the following command to create a new tree in the <code>trees</code> directory:</p><pre>forester new --dir=trees --prefix=xxx</pre><p>If the last tree in this directory was <code>xxx-0039</code>, a new tree will be generated at <code>xxx-003A</code>. The new tree will be populated with a correct <code>\date</code> declaration.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>43590</anchor> <rss>jms-0071.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0071</addr>  <route>jms-0071.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>14</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="jms-006Z.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006Z" title="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</link> › tree title completion for tool support</title> <parent>jms-006Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A new <code>forester complete</code> command has been added to search for trees by their title; the purpose of this command is to facilitate external tool support, such as this <link href="https://github.com/rileyshahar/cmp-Forester" type="external">proof-of-concept completion engine for neovim</link>. Please browse <code>forester complete --help</code> for more information about this command.</p><p>Current limitations: the command is currently case sensitive and only searches prefixes; in the future, it would be desirable to support more flexible <link href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Approximate_string_matching" type="external">fuzzy-search</link>.</p><p>Thanks to <link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local" addr="rileyshahar" title="Riley Shahar">Riley Shahar</link> for implementing this feature.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>43591</anchor> <rss>jms-0072.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0072</addr>  <route>jms-0072.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>14</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="jms-006Z.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006Z" title="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</link> › rudimentary support for XML attributes</title> <parent>jms-006Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <link href="jms-005P.xml" type="local" addr="jms-005P" title="Forester">Forester</link> encounters an undefined function, it automatically passes through to the XML output. For instance, if the function <code>\myfun</code> is not defined, then the <link href="jms-005P.xml" type="local" addr="jms-005P" title="Forester">Forester</link> code <code>\myfun{hello}</code> will render to the XML code <code>&lt;myfun&gt;hello&lt;/myfun&gt;</code>. <strong>The <link href="jms-006Z.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006Z" title="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</link> extends this fall-through behavior to support XML attributes.</strong></p><p>In particular, if you write <code>\myfun{key1}{value1}{key2}{value2}{hello}</code>, <link href="jms-005P.xml" type="local" addr="jms-005P" title="Forester">Forester</link> will render the following XML code:</p><pre>&lt;myfun key1=&quot;value1&quot; key2=&quot;value2&quot;&gt;
  hello
&lt;/myfun&gt;</pre><p>Thanks to <link href="masanoriogino.xml" type="local" addr="masanoriogino" title="Masanori Ogino">Masanori Ogino</link> for suggesting this feature, and welcome to the <link href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss" type="external"><link href="jms-005P.xml" type="local" addr="jms-005P" title="Forester">Forester</link> community</link>!.</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>In addition to the major changes above, the following minor changes are included in this release:</p><ol><li>A <code>title</code> attribute attribute has been added to the XML output of internal links, in order to facilitate tooltips and other affordances in rendered forests. Thanks to <link href="armaëlguéneau.xml" type="local" addr="armaëlguéneau" title="Armaël Guéneau">Armaël Guéneau</link> for implementing this feature.</li>
  <li>Subdirectories of input directories will now be traversed automatically; note that the tree address model remains flat, and subdirectories are present only for convenience.</li>
  <li>Added a nicer command line interface with <code>--help</code> documentation.</li>
  <li>I have migrated much of the system code to use the experimental <link href="https://github.com/ocaml-multicore/eio" type="external">Eio library</link> for improved portability.</li>
  <li>The example forest has been removed from the main repository, and moved into a separate <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forest-template" type="external">template repository</link>.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>43592</anchor> <rss>jms-0071.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0071</addr>  <route>jms-0071.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>14</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="jms-006Z.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006Z" title="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</link> › tree title completion for tool support</title> <parent>jms-006Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A new <code>forester complete</code> command has been added to search for trees by their title; the purpose of this command is to facilitate external tool support, such as this <link href="https://github.com/rileyshahar/cmp-Forester" type="external">proof-of-concept completion engine for neovim</link>. Please browse <code>forester complete --help</code> for more information about this command.</p><p>Current limitations: the command is currently case sensitive and only searches prefixes; in the future, it would be desirable to support more flexible <link href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Approximate_string_matching" type="external">fuzzy-search</link>.</p><p>Thanks to <link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local" addr="rileyshahar" title="Riley Shahar">Riley Shahar</link> for implementing this feature.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>